Messages.Value: Thank you for calling the travel agency, my name is Mason, how may I assist you today?

Hi Mason, my name is Sarah Davis and I'm calling because I have an issue with my travel plans. I recently booked a trip from New York City to Los Angeles and I'm having trouble finding my hotel reservation.
I'm sorry to hear that Sarah. Can you please provide me with your hotel name and reservation number?
Sure, the hotel is called the Westin and my reservation number is 12345678. The check-in date is January 20th.
Thank you for that information, Sarah. I'm going to look into this for you. While I do that, can you please confirm your departure date and time and airline information?
My flight is with Delta Airlines, flight number 123, departing from JFK on January 18th at 8:00 AM.

Thank you, Sarah. I'm sorry to hear about the inconvenience you're experiencing and I understand how frustrating that can be. Let me check on your hotel reservation and I will get back to you momentarily.
Thank you, Mason. I appreciate your help.

Thank you for your patience, Sarah. I was able to find your reservation at the Westin Hotel for January 20th. It seems that there was a system error that caused your reservation to not show up in your account. I apologize for the inconvenience and frustration this may have caused.
Oh, I see. Thank you for letting me know, Mason. Is there anything else I can do to make sure this doesn't happen again in the future?
At this point in time, I recommend contacting us if you experience any issues with your bookings. We will be happy to assist you in any way we can. Is there anything else I can help you with?
No, that's all for now. Thank you so much for your help, Mason. I appreciate it.
You're welcome, Sarah. Have a great trip!
